This paper deals with optimization techniques for Gaussian processes, which are commonly used in machine learning and data analysis. Specifically, the paper proposes a Quadratic Unconstrained Binary Optimization (QUBO) model for selecting the set of locations to take measurements in order to reduce the posterior variance of the Gaussian process. This problem falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures (cs.DS), control systems (cs.SY), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
